{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641265","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641265"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:25:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:25:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17876"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17876","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17876"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.18,0.67,0.02,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10590"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78726"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10590","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10590"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17876"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64069"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10069"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24685"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24687"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78726","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78726"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EObesity affects multiple organ systems, particularly the cardiovascular system. Understanding the relationship between lipid metabolism and cardiac function is crucial for comprehending obesity-related heart disease.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the relationship between lipid metabolism and cardiac function?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cardiac lipid accumulation enhances myocardial relaxation","Lipoprotein lipase is predominantly expressed in liver tissue","Obesity-related lipid deposition impairs cardiac relaxation","Cardiac contractility improves with myocardial fat deposition","Lipoprotein lipase expression is restricted to cardiac tissue"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObesity-related lipid deposition impairs cardiac relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E through several mechanisms. Excess lipid accumulation in cardiomyocytes can lead to lipotoxicity, affecting both diastolic and systolic function of the heart.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECardiac lipid accumulation enhances myocardial relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E - Lipid accumulation actually impairs cardiac relaxation and contractility\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELipoprotein lipase is predominantly expressed in liver tissue\u003C/strong\u003E - Lipoprotein lipase is primarily expressed in adipose tissue and skeletal muscle, not the liver\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECardiac contractility improves with myocardial fat deposition\u003C/strong\u003E - Fat deposition impairs rather than improves contractility\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELipoprotein lipase expression is restricted to cardiac tissue\u003C/strong\u003E - Lipoprotein lipase is mainly expressed in adipose tissue and skeletal muscle, not exclusively in cardiac tissue\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these relationships is important as obesity is a significant risk factor for heart failure, partially through direct effects of cardiac lipid accumulation on myocardial function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Lipoprotein lipase is primarily expressed in adipose tissue and skeletal muscle, where it hydrolyses triglycerides from circulating lipoproteins.","Excess lipid accumulation in obesity can impair cardiac relaxation (diastolic function) and contractility.","Obesity is a significant risk factor for heart failure through multiple mechanisms including cardiac lipid accumulation."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Chandel NS. Lipid Metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Sep 1;13(9):a040576. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a040576. PMID: 34470787; PMCID: PMC8411952","Wakil SJ, Abu-Elheiga LA. Fatty acid metabolism: target for metabolic syndrome. J Lipid Res. 2009 Apr;50 Suppl(Suppl):S138-43. doi: 10.1194/jlr.R800079-JLR200. Epub 2008 Dec 1. PMID: 19047759; PMCID: PMC2674721"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64069"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17876"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64069","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64069"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T15:06:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T15:43:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10590"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78726"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{